</p>

---

## 🚀 Features

* 🕹️ Simple UI navigation system
* 🎮 Built-in game (Ping Pong / Pong)
* 📟 1.3" OLED display (SH1106 / SSD1306)
* 🎛️ Button-based controls
* 🔊 Buzzer for sound effects
* 📊 MPU6050 sensor support (motion / tilt)
* 🔋 Battery powered (3.7V Li-ion)
* ⚡ DC-DC boost converter (3.7V → 5V)

---

## 🧰 Hardware Used

* **ESP32 (WROOM / similar)**
* **MPU6050** (accelerometer + gyroscope)
* **OLED 1.3" display** (I2C)
* **Push buttons** (multiple GPIO inputs)
* **Buzzer**
* **3.7V Li-ion battery**
* **DC-DC boost converter (MT3608 or similar)**

---

## 🔌 Pin Configuration (example)

| Component     | GPIO           |
| ------------- | -------------- |
| OLED SDA      | 18             |
| OLED SCL      | 19             |
| Button UP     | 27             |
| Button DOWN   | 26             |
| Other buttons | 14, 25, 33, 13 |
| Buzzer        | 23             |
| Battery ADC   | (custom pin)   |

> ⚠️ Pins may differ depending on your wiring

---

## 🧠 Software Architecture

Project is structured in modular way:

* `AppManager` – controls app lifecycle
* `DisplayManager` – OLED rendering
* `InputManager` – button handling with debounce
* `BatteryManager` – voltage + percentage calculation
* `Apps/` – separate applications (games, info screen, etc.)

---

## 🎮 Game Example

### Ping Pong (Pong)

* Player controls paddle using buttons
* AI bot with adjustable difficulty
* Levels system (planned / implemented)
* Score tracking
* Sound feedback

---

## 🔋 Battery

* Powered by **3.7V Li-ion**
* Boosted to **5V** via DC-DC converter
* Battery voltage is read via ADC and resistors
* Percentage is calculated based on voltage range

Example:

* Min: ~2.4V
* Max: ~3.3V (after divider)

---

## 🛠️ Setup & Build

### Requirements

* [PlatformIO](https://platformio.org/)
* VS Code

### Build

```bash
pio run
```

### Upload

```bash
pio run --target upload
```

### Monitor

```bash
pio device monitor
```

---

## 📦 Project Structure

```
/src
  /apps
  /core
  /ui
  main.cpp

/include
  /apps
  /core
  /ui
  config.h

platformio.ini
diagram.json
wokwi.toml (for simulation)
```

---

## 🧪 Simulation

Project supports **Wokwi simulation**
Make sure `wokwi.toml` is in the root folder.

